    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog provides a high-floor opportunity to capitalize on favorable matchups against mid-rotation arms. The strongest play on the board is **Lawrence Butler**, who earns a 73.28 efficiency score leading off against Clay Holmes. **Butler**\u2019s profile is bolstered by a massive +13% dynamic platoon edge and the optimal leadoff spot, making him a prime candidate to anchor our R/SB output. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (72.15) and **Tyler Freeman** (70.04) follow closely behind; **Freeman** is a particularly intriguing start against Buehler, as the combination of a high-xERA opponent and a slow delivery allows us to leverage his speed potential, adding +2% to his score based on steal probability.\n\nWhile the core lineup is performing well, our bench decisions reflect a conservative approach to daily game caps. **Gavin Sheets** was the most difficult exclusion, finishing with a 59.39 score that was ultimately edged out by the superior platoon and park factors surrounding **Cal Raleigh** and **Jeremiah Jackson**. While **Sheets** benefits from a strong +17% SP skill boost against Sugano, he lacks the ceiling that **Jeremiah Jackson** offers in a hitter-friendly environment today. We are also monitoring the status of **Yainer Diaz**, who remains on the bench due to a pending lineup confirmation; his 56.34 score is suppressed by an assumed #8 spot, but he remains a high-variance pivot if a late-order promotion occurs.\n\nStrategically, we are leaning heavily into the +16% park factors afforded to **Luis Arraez**, **Matt Chapman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Taylor Ward** in their respective contests against Baz. **Chapman** and **Lee** specifically gain an extra edge from the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which is vital given our focus on the scarcest category, stolen bases. We advise caution regarding **Cal Raleigh**; while his 59.98 score qualifies him as a start, he faces a slight -6% penalty due to platoon dynamics, making him the most volatile asset in today's batting order. Otherwise, the indicators are aligned for a productive day of Roto gains.",
